        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/ba9def/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-03-09T01:08:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened with Lamb and this was singing after a few hours! Pretty classic with olives / bacon fat but had more sensibility (less rusric) than some other bottles.</p>\n<p>Tannins have subsided and frankly this was way better than a 2006 La Geynale opened a few weeks back. I wonder if that wine needs more time?</p>\n<p>Overall a really good bottle from the last vintage of a legend</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
